@api.hangfire_HostAddress = http://localhost:5212

### Fan-out: enqueue N worker jobs in parallel
### Returns immediately with job IDs — jobs run in background
### Browse /hangfire to watch them execute
### Fan-out: submit 3 orders — each order processed by an independent job.
### If the same order ID is already being processed, the duplicate job will retry until the first finishes.
POST {{api.hangfire_HostAddress}}/api/fanout
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "orders": [
    { "id": 1, "customerName": "Alice", "amount": 99.99 },
    { "id": 2, "customerName": "Bob",   "amount": 149.50 },
    { "id": 3, "customerName": "Carol", "amount": 19.00 }
  ]
}

###

### Check the state of a single job (replace JOB_ID with an id from the fan-out response)
GET {{api.hangfire_HostAddress}}/api/fanout/status/JOB_ID
Accept: application/json

###

### Two-stage pipeline: Transform → Prepare+Zip → Fan-out SFTP uploads
### Each entity gets its own TransformJob → PrepareJob → N SftpUploadJobs
POST {{api.hangfire_HostAddress}}/api/fanout/pipeline
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "entityIds": [101, 102, 103]
}

###
